com.immortallabs.cardboard.game
Class Deck

java.lang.Object
  com.immortallabs.cardboard.game.Deck

public class Deck
extends java.lang.Object

Models a stack of CardBoard cards in a random order. You can deal card off the deck and ask the deck if it's empty.

Operations:
  • Cards can be dealt off the deck.
  • The deck can be asked whether or not it is empty.

Version:
1.4, 1/18/09
Author:
Kyle Williamson, Formerly Sky Eckstrom, ImmortalLabs CSC308 W09
See Also:

addNumCol

private java.util.ArrayList<Card> addNumCol(Card.NUMBER num,
                                            Card.COLOR col)
A private method used by createDeck to remove duplicate code used in the creation of both normal decks and beginner decks. Automatically adds the correct shapes and fills to the deck.

Parameters:
num - The number of shapes to be added in the Cards.
col - The color of the shapes to be added in the Cards.
Returns:
A set of the cards used in the Deck.

createDeck

private void createDeck(boolean normDeck)
Creates the Cards used in a deck. If a normal size deck it has 81 cards and 3 different Numbers, Colors, Shapes, and Fills. If it's a beginner deck it has 27 cards, 3 different Numbers, Shapes, and Fills but only one Color

Parameters:
normDeck - A boolean to determine if a normal size deck is created or a beginner deck.

deal

public Card deal()
Deals the top card off the deck. Returns null if there are no more cards in the deck.

Returns:
the top card of the Deck or null if the deck is empty.
